# Accepted-risk register for Trivy image scans (ci.yml gate + image-scan.yml gate).
#
# Every entry MUST carry: the CVE id, why it is accepted (not exploitable here /
# no fix released / mitigation in place), an owner, and an expiry date — re-justify
# or remove it when the date passes. Unexplained entries are a review reject.
# Entries only silence the FAILING gates; the full report and SARIF still show them.
#
# Format (one per line):
#   CVE-2026-XXXXX  # <owner> <YYYY-MM-DD expiry>: <why this is acceptable>
